Bluetongue, Switzerland
-----------------------
Information received on [and dated] 1 Feb 2019 from Mr. Hans Wyss, Chief Veterinary Officer, Schwarzenburgstrasse 161, Swiss Federal Veterinary Office, Liebefeld Berne, Switzerland

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report no. 14
Date of start of the event: 19 Oct 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 23 Oct 2017
Report date: 1 Feb 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 1 Feb 2019
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: March 2010
Manifestation of disease: Subclinical infection [but see "Affected population" further]
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 8
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1 (BT_2018_14_SO): Lommiswil, Lommiswil, Lebern, Solothurn
Date of start of the outbreak: 16 Oct 2018
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 26 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0
Affected population: Clinical signs, not surveillance program [see comments].

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors

Epidemiological comments
Update 25 Jan 2019: Delayed notification from October 2018. One outbreak of BTV-8 in sheep on a farm in Solothurn. One animal showed clinical signs and was killed.

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, quarantine, selective killing and disposal, zoning, disinfection, control of vectors, slaughter, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Institute of Virology and Immunology (IVI) (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep / Reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 29 Oct 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

